<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="19" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Judd</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 16.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-10-21"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 21, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of September 24 (No. 8) has
                            been received. It treats of many matters interesting, though not of
                            chief importance. Your proceedings in regard to them are approved.
                            Disunion, by surprise and impetuous passion, took the first successes,
                            and profited by them to make public opinion in Europe. Union comes
                            forward more slowly, but with greater and more enduring vigor. This
                            nation, like every other, in the present as in all other cases, stands
                            by its own strength. Other powers will respect it so long as it exhibits
                            its ability to defend and save itself. More, perhaps, ought not to be
                            wished; certainly it could not be reasonably expected.</p>
                        <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">N. B Judd</hi>, Esq.,<lb/><hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., Berlin</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>